laboratory_examinations.findings: Moderate bilateral nonhemorrhagic pleural effusions; multiple subcentimeter hypodensities in the liver unchanged from prior; 3 mm hypodensity in the lower pole of the left kidney; hyperdense fluid extending from the right pericolic gutter into the pelvis compatible with hemoperitoneum. No areas of focal contrast extravasation to suggest active bleed.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: New moderate bilateral nonhemorrhagic pleural effusions; multiple subcentimeter hypodensities in the liver unchanged from prior.
